{"type":"text","text":"When the value of this property is "},{"code":"YES","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and the map is tilted, the annotation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view appears smaller if it is towards the top of the view (closer to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"horizon) and larger if it is towards the bottom of the view (closer to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"viewpoint). This is also the behavior of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationImage"},{"type":"text","text":" objects. When the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"value of this property is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NO"},{"type":"text","text":" or the map’s pitch is zero, the annotation view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"remains the same size regardless of its position on-screen.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default value of this property is "},{"code":"NO","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Keep this property set to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NO"},{"type":"text","text":" if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the view’s legibility is important."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scaling many on-screen annotation views can contribute to poor map"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"performance. Consider keeping this property disabled if your use case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"involves hundreds or thousands of annotation views."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/scalesWithViewingDistance":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/scaleswithviewingdistance","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/scalesWithViewingDistance","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Boolean value that determines whether the annotation view grows and shrinks"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the distance between the viewpoint and the annotation view changes on a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tilted map."}],"title":"scalesWithViewingDistance","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"scalesWithViewingDistance"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","title":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\